I can understand if you're really trying to kill something big, then yeah, play it properly, but if it's part of your character...<br>
<br>
For every Jesus Christ, there has to be a Dr Nick to match <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Just thought I'd tag something on the end.  In my experience, a well played cleric is invaluable. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=bakanome>Bakanome</A> at: 2/21/02 5:55:58 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usteeltoefv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SteeltoeFV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/21/02 6:00:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1416.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Clerics</span><hr size=1> Bakanome - Actually the advise I offer is sound advise for any server (roleplaying or not). Once you join a group you should be 'expected' to play your class to the best of its ability.<br>
<br>
Why would anyone want to be deep in SolA killing the Evil Nasty Gnomes and have some joker think his cleric should be meleeing with 0 mana as you are all dying a horrible death when all you needed was a cleric who would sit down, med for mana and heal people...<br>
<br>
Thats all Im saying <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Im just trying to teach others who are not truely experienced in the game of EQ 'There Role In There Class'.... <p><B>Steeltoe Stonegrinder</B><i> Guardian of Kaladim and Slayer of Ogres</I><BR>
Level 20 Dwarven Warrior<BR>
<BR>
<B>Steelfaith Stonegrinder</B><I> Acolyte of the Holy Brell</I><BR>
Level 20 Dwarven Cleric<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/utirga006.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tirga006</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/21/02 6:26:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1416.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Clerics</span><hr size=1> Actually I don't really agree with that entirely, while I love clerics (I really do) they just aren't &quot;needed&quot; unless there is a major raid or anything, for experience a Bard is optimal. Later we get group Rune, for about 40 Points while healing for 40 a tick, this often keeps the group at full health ( or neer it).<br>
<br>
I have nothing against clerics, I just like to break the &quot;holy trinity&quot;. One nice thing about clerics that I like is it allowed me to bring my mele skills up for a while... Using my 2 dmg song and healsong I could not use my weapon in 3 levels and frankly I like to keep my skillz up to par... when the cleric got low on mana I just switched back to all Instrument again.<br>
<br>
If you don't beleive me just post the question on www.eqdiva.com webpage in the discussion section... see what responces you get. Perhaps you haven't grouped with only &quot;good bard&quot;.<br>
<br>
A good bard is defined by one that can twist 3 songs, a really good bard is one that choses the one based on experience and recomendations. A GREAT bard is one that does both of these and used techniques that no one else has, and gets away with it. *sight*<br>
<br>
I may not have &quot;a really high level character&quot; but I listen to my elders and experiment.<br>
<br>
Of course I hope no one is offended... just my views and experience. I have found myself very usefull in groups of people at least 20 levels higher...<br>
<br>
Sorry, I got carried away again...<br>
<br>
Tirga level 21 Bard Fironia Vie<br>
Carlota level 29 Bard Tallos Zek<br>
Marxist Level 24 bard Rallos Zek<br>
<br>
Edit: Forgot to ask... I didn't see DS, Runes, Slows (when no Shaman), or charm (A true lifesaver if I ever saw one... ever save a clerics life much?)...there are much more... of course... their versitility is an asset <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/utirga006.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tirga006</A> at: 2/21/02 6:31:17 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubjond.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bjond</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 515<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/21/02 6:57:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1416.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Actually, Tirga, ..</span><hr size=1> .. he's mostly right.  Cleric CH + Warrior HP == great group.  You can get away with a shaman as main healer for xp groups and (rarely) a druid, but that's about it.  Group rune can keep you alive long enough for the cleric to med up for another heal or to limp along for some gimpy xp, especially if your tank can self-heal.  Odd groups can work, they just don't work as well as groups with a real healer (cleric or shaman).  Don't get me wrong, I love bards to bits.  I've grouped with some amazing bards.  But, bards are not combat healers -- not even close.<br>
<br>
However, bards are wonderful additions to just about any group.  I disagree about the 4-5 bards tops comment.  We had about 6 or so high level bards.  People would fight over who got the bard in their group at raids.  Get a bard on a dragon raid and it means your group will live (resist song, mana song, rune song).  Any time a bard logged on and said, &quot;any groups need me?&quot;, the reply was instant.  Bard AE groups are amazing.  A 5 person group (bard, monk, sham, sk, cleric) completely cleared disco 1&amp;2 of old-seb in about 3 pulls using the bard AE damage song.  We had to sit about waiting for the area to respawn.  By comparison, wizard AE is pathetic -- you end up waiting on the wizard/s to med and if you don't have an enchanter to AE stun/mez, you can't do it.<br>
<br>
BTW, good clerics are nice, too.  Hell, a skilled player of any class is nice.  FV has a ton of first time players.  A lot of them will become highly skilled, but it takes some time and they need folks like you to help them get there, Steeltoe. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=bakanome>Bakanome</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 20<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/21/02 7:02:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1416.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Actually, Tirga, ..</span><hr size=1> Take it from me.  Druids are HORRIBLE healers.  I was often forced to be a healer back on the old server.  Absolutely horrible job, used up my mana like nothing else, for so little regen.  I was always glad for a cleric nearby.  It meant I could use my mana for easier things like buffs, damage shields, harmony and nuking.  Also, I was sort of an emergency damage absorber if the first tank was really badly hurt (if we only had one tank) I'd melee the gimp for a couple of seconds trying to draw him off.  Being clad in full leather armour helped me take damage much better than the pure casters, giving the good old cleric some time to get our tank back into the fight.  Of course, I was never a health concern, just jumped straight into treeform and was good as new a minute later. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usteeltoefv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SteeltoeFV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 22<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/21/02 7:07:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1416.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Actually, Tirga, ..</span><hr size=1> Bjond - I do not wish ANYONE to get me wrong. Bards are needed, but are not needed in great numbers like Clerics/Warriors/Rogues and Wizards. So when your guild tends to have a 'cap' on how many people it would like in the guild you have to trim numbers somewhere and that somewhere is usually in the Magician and Bard area... you really do not need 10 bards in a guild to make encounters successful. Thats all I was saying...<br>
<br>
Bards kick ass, but they have there place and many play them well...<br>
<br>
An example would be Crip... twisting 5 songs... he is a manimal....<br>
<br>
Bards a GREAT addition to any group... but if I want mana and crowd control Im going for an Enchanter (*IF* I had to choose...)<br>
<br>
Again... do not read between my lines.... all classes have there places... Im just trying to shed some light on 'generally speaking' what your role in your class is. <p><B>Steeltoe Stonegrinder</B><i> Guardian of Kaladim and Slayer of Ogres</I><BR>
