Level 20 Dwarven Cleric<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubjond.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bjond</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 517<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/21/02 7:08:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1416.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Most druids specialize in evocation</span><hr size=1> That's why most are awful healers.  I knew a druid that specialized in alteration.  She was merely bad as a healer, not awful.  Still better than a bard for healing, though.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/utirga006.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tirga006</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/21/02 7:23:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1416.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Actually, Tirga, ..</span><hr size=1> I hate to throw numbers at you ... but here it goes quickly<br>
