{Bards Rule!}  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usulig.showPublicProfile?language=EN>sulig</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 31<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/21/02 7:30:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1416.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Actually, Tirga, ..</span><hr size=1> Steeltoe, I just wanted to let you know there is at least one other cleric out there. This is my first serious attempt at playing a cleric, but I have plenty of EQ experience. I have also played a shaman as my main in the past. While this is very different from playing a cleric, I think I have a pretty good idea of how to play one because of the experience of playing the shaman and noting the differences between myuself and my cleric friends. I hope that made sense. I have every intention of playing this cleric for a very long time and seeing 60 and beyond with him. I have several RL friends I am playing with so it makes it a lot easier to play a cleric on this server though. Just letting you know you are not the only one out there.<br>
